{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "STAR, proposed by Xu et al. (2019) in 2018, is another end-to-end framework inspired by multi-instance tags.",
    "The framework is a generative representation of actions called instance patterns aggregated by attentional mechanisms, and learns temporal relationships between them through a recursive neural network (Shi et al. 2015).",
    "Actions can be predicted and localized in time by designing a scoring term fused with attention weights (ST-GradCAM).",
    "In 2021, Huang et al. (2021) proposed an FAC-Net framework based on the I3D trunk.",
    "Three branches are attached to the framework: the class foreground classification branch, the class-independent attention branch, and the multi-instance learning branch."
  ],
